Name: Label
Description: A display label for the number range. May be expressed in multiple languages. Repeat for labels with different content, for example, labels with differing length limitations.

Name: Low
Description: The lower bound of the range expressed in the datatype xs:decimal. If not present, then there is no lower bound.

Name: LowDouble
Description: The lower bound of the range expressed in the datatype xs:double. If not present, then there is no lower bound.

Name: High
Description: The upper bound of the range in the datatype xs:decimal. If not present, then there is no upper bound.

Name: HighDouble
Description: The upper bound of the range in the datatype xs:double. If not present, then there is no upper bound.

Name: TopCode
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or greater than this value has been coded as the top-code value. Expressed in the datatype xs:decimal.

Name: TopCodeDouble
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or greater than this value has been coded as the top-code value. Expressed in the datatype xs:decimal.

Name: BottomCode
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or less than this value has been coded as the bottom-code value. Expressed in the datatype xs:double.

Name: BottomCodeDouble
Description: Indicates that any response equal to or less than this value has been coded as the bottom-code value. Expressed in the datatype xs:double.

Name: RegExp
Description: Regular expression defining the allowed syntax of the number.
